This spontaneous case report was received via courtesy from Sanofi-Aventis (Mfg no: 1-695422287) on 16-Mar-
2015, and is referring to a female consumer of unspecified age in the UNITED STATES, who received 
BETASERON (interferon beta - 1b) and had JOHN CUNNINGHAM VIRUS POSITIVE and BETASERON 
THERAPIES FAILED.
No information was given on consumer's medical history, past drugs, concurrent conditions. It was not reported 
whether consumer received any concomitant medication.
On an unspecified date, the consumer started BETASERON (interferon beta - 1b). Product lot number and 
expiration date was not provided. It was not reported whether BETASERON was used previously. 
The consumer reported that BETASERON THERAPIES FAILED since the start date. It was also reported that 
